{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-js","path":"/module1","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"courseId":"LeapFROGS"}},"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"exercise","properties":{"id":"1","title":"Why Python?"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You might be wondering why you should be learning Python."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Python is widely used in the scientific community and it is a great tool to help you further advance your geosciences research."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We will present you with the most important reasons to start using Python in the following "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://foundations.projectpythia.org/foundations/why-python.html"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"link"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Convinced? Now, it’s time to install Python on your local machine. You can follow "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.datacamp.com/blog/how-to-install-python"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"this guide"}]},{"type":"text","value":". We recommend going through Anaconda for Mac, Linux and Windows machines as this will make the setup easier. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"exercise","properties":{"id":"2","title":"Getting Started with Python"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now that you know why you should be learning Python, let’s get started! One of the first thing you usually do when learning a new computer language is to print “Hello World” to make sure that everything has been installed correctly. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In Python, all you have to do is write "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"print(\"Hello World!\")"}]},{"type":"text","value":". So let’s try this with another sentence. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Be patient - it might take a few minutes the first time you run the code. But it usually speeds up."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Question:"}]},{"type":"text","value":" Print “I love doing geoscience research with Python” on the console."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"codeblock","properties":{"id":"01_01"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Remember the print command!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"exercise","properties":{"id":"3","title":"Numbers"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let’s start about learning number and math with Python. Although "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://numpy.org"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"numpy"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is the most widely used library to deal with math for science purposes, it is good to start with the basics of what Python offers out of the box."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Number in Python works pretty much like everywhere else and the basic math that you have learned will apply to Python. Follow the links to look at the basic operation:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://docs.trinket.io/getting-started-with-python#/numbers/numbers-in-python"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Numbers in Python"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://docs.trinket.io/getting-started-with-python#/numbers/addition-subtraction-multiplication-division"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Addition, sutraction, multiplication, division"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://docs.trinket.io/getting-started-with-python#/numbers/mods"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Modulus operations"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://docs.trinket.io/getting-started-with-python#/numbers/exponents"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Exponents"}]},{"type":"text","value":" - This one can be a little tricky in Python"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://docs.trinket.io/getting-started-with-python#/numbers/order-of-operations"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Order of Operations"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type"